<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC4FFEBA2207C42936A0BE2" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="1226" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC4FFEBA2207C42936A0BE2" blockId="13.[809,1424,1816,1899]" lastBlockId="14.[163,779,197,403]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="1226" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC4FFE8A2207C4293CA0D5C" box="[809,938,1816,1837]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Medium adult-sized 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC4FFE8A5B57C4295F00D5F" authorityName="Steenstrup" authorityYear="1857" box="[1212,1424,1816,1838]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ommastrephidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Ommastrephidae</taxonomicName>
without photophores; funnel groove without foveola; tentacles without carpal locking apparatus; tentacle club with manus horny rings with homogeneous dentition; four series of suckers on dactylus; lateral suckers of the paralarva proboscis equal in diameter to the central ones; paralarval development more advanced at hatching than other ommastrephids; paralarvae with skin sculpture; adult female with multiple seminal receptacles in the buccal membrane.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
